=================
About this script
=================

This script is used for create the host configuration in nagios.

------
How to
------

You can use this script two ways.

1. Use command line create one host at one time.
-p specify the path of faurecia-nagios-configuration if you have more than one repo on your computer.Or you can ignore it, the script can find it automatic.
-a specify the use.
-n specify the host_name.
-i specify the address.
-P specify the parents.
-s specify the hostgroups.

eg:
./create.py -a ohtpl_area_as -a ohtpl_env_test -a bhtpl_app_microsp_win -n EUEDCSWTH05M -i 127.0.0.1/cabrpvmw0002.brp.ca.corp -p CLUSTER_SAP_FP3 -s sys_vmware_asadcvct0002 -s inc_vmware_esx_memory -P /home/chengca/faurecia-nagios-configuration

2. Use file create a lots of hosts at one time.
-m  0 means use dns as the address
    1 means use the ip as the address.
-f  specify the file, Not include the suffix.
    Multiple files use -f file1 -f file2 ..
    There are two files use this name.
    One for the hostname and address.
    One for configuration file.
    For example, as.txt and as.cfg.
    You can write all the host in asia in as.txt, and all the server use the same configuration in as.cfg.

eg:
./create.py -m 0 -f as -f eu -f us

---------
Attention
---------
This script is just part of another project.
If you just use this script to create the host.
Please remember to checkout the your branch in faurecia-nagios-configuration first.
